The 10 mana per INT point is a loose guideline to quickly tally your mana.<br>
<br>
The equation that most mana calculators use is:<br>
<br>
(((INT/5)+2)*Level)+mana items<br>
<br>
EX<br>
<br>
200/5 = 40<br>
40+2=42<br>
42*60=2520<br>
<br>
So, at level 60 with 200 INT you'll have 2520 base mana.<br>
<br>
There is some debate as to whether the +2 should be a +1, but in any case the difference would be minor.<br>
<br>
Current theory says for every point above 200 you get mana on a 1 to 1 ratio.  Some recent parsing has challenged this but, again, the difference would be minor.<br>
<br>
EX.<br>
227 INT = 27 extra mana<br>
<br>
Right now I'm sitting at 227 INT with roughly 1100 in +mana gear.<br>
<br>
2520+1100+27=3647 mana<br>
<br>
Hope this helps.  Again a lot of this is unconfirmed as VI won't own up to the equations they use for determing our mana pool.<br>
<br>
And, yes, WIS casters apparently use the same formula.<br>
